\index{Frequency, cutoff}
 

All low-pass filters are rated at a certain \textit{cutoff frequency}.  That is, the frequency above which the output voltage falls below 70.7\% of the input voltage.  This cutoff percentage of 70.7 is not really arbitrary, all though it may seem so at first glance.  In a simple capacitive/resistive low-pass filter, it is the frequency at which capacitive reactance in ohms equals resistance in ohms.  In a simple capacitive low-pass filter (one resistor, one capacitor), the cutoff frequency is given as:
 

 
\includegraphics{12097.eps} 
 

