\index{Winding, secondary}
 

It is easy to demonstrate simple transformer action using SPICE, setting up the primary and secondary windings of the simulated transformer as a pair of ``mutual'' inductors. (Figure~\ref{02132.eps})  The coefficient of magnetic field coupling is given at the end of the ``\texttt{k}'' line in the SPICE circuit description, this example being set very nearly at perfection (1.000).  This coefficient describes how closely ``linked'' the two inductors are, magnetically.  The better these two inductors are magnetically coupled, the more efficient the energy transfer between them should be. 
 

 
